problem:
Determine whether the following claim is true:

Let $f_1,..., f_N:X\longrightarrow \mathbb{R}^+$ be a set of bounded functions and suppose that for each $i=1,...,N$, there exists a sequence of functions $\{g_{n,i}\}_{n\in\mathbb{N}}$ such that $g_{n,i}\downarrow f_i$ pointwise. Define the sequence $\{g_n\}_{n\in\mathbb{N}}$ of functions by:
\begin{equation*}
g_n:= \max_{i\le N} g_{n,i} \qquad \forall n\in\mathbb{N}
\end{equation*}
Then $g_{n}\downarrow \max_{i\le N} f_i$ pointwise.

